data.title: Morte is a new operator in Call of Duty: Modern Warfare and Warzone
data.meta_description: Italian rapper Fabio Rovazzi lends his vocal talent to the role.
data.text:
Call of Duty: Warzone Pacific

REVIEW. Written by Ben Lyons on the 15th of December 2021 at 11

Caldera is here, but does its addition advance the popular battle royale title enough?

Call of Duty: Warzone

REVIEW. Written by Eirik Hyldbakk Furu on the 13th of March 2020 at 12

Infinity Ward delivers one of the best battle royales out there although it does very little to set itself apart.

Call of Duty: Warzone removes snowballs for being too OP

NEWS. Written by Alex Hopley on the 22nd of December 2023 at 15:32

A truly lethal snowball fight took place in the Warzone Gulag.

Call of Duty: Warzone is being shut down in September

NEWS. Written by Ben Lyons on the 23rd of June 2023 at 15:39

Warzone is dead. Long live Warzone 2.0.

Call of Duty: Warzone is back online, but as Call of Duty: Warzone Caldera

NEWS. Written by Samuel Lakin on the 30th of November 2022 at 15:35

Taken offline temporarily as Warzone 2 released, it's come back a little different.

The final Call of Duty: Warzone update has arrived

NEWS. Written by Ben Lyons on the 29th of September 2022 at 13:16

It's full steam ahead to Warzone 2.0 now.

Artist claims the Floofy Fury skin in Call of Duty has been plagiarised

NEWS. Written by Petter Hegevall on the 2nd of August 2022 at 16:35

"I am very disappointed to see my work being plagiarised by a big company like Activision in this way."

World Series of Warzone 2022 announced

ESPORTS. Written by Ben Lyons on the 27th of July 2022 at 09

It'll feature $600,000 in prize money, as well as an in-game open qualifier format.
